The paper deals with the k-server problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it discusses the competitive ratio of algorithms. Information theory (cs.IT) is relevant as the paper talks about potential-based algorithms. Machine learning (cs.LG) may also be relevant as the paper mentions a joint work with M\k{a}dry, who is a well-known researcher in the field of machine learning. Finally, the paper involves optimization (cs.SI) as it aims to improve the competitive ratio of the k-server problem.
